// Semantic direction:
// optimizer gives bytecode a transformation path before execution.
// optimize_pass describes one ordered optimization step.
// profile_counter records repeated execution behavior.
// hot_path identifies bytecode regions worth specializing.
// inline_cache stores fast lookup results for repeated dispatch.
// specialization creates optimized forms for observed runtime types and values.
// guard_check verifies optimized assumptions before running compiled paths.
// deoptimize returns execution to generic bytecode when assumptions fail.
// compiled_trace and native_stub describe JIT-produced execution fragments.
// fallback_path preserves correctness when optimization cannot apply.

// Primitive flow:
// execution_loop -> profile_counter -> hot_path
// -> metadata_table + inspect_value
// -> optimize_pass + specialization + inline_cache
// -> jit + compiled_trace + guard_check
// -> native_stub or fallback_path
// -> result

// This extends the reflective runtime with optimization and JIT-specialization semantics.

