// Semantic direction:
// source_unit gives the compiler a concrete program input boundary.
// token_stream, parser, and ast define the source-to-tree path.
// semantic_check validates names, types, and runtime constraints before lowering.
// lower_ast transforms high-level syntax into VM-oriented forms.
// bytecode_builder emits executable instructions, constants, and symbols.
// bytecode_module packages bytecode for linking and loading.
// bootstrap defines the path from seed runtime into self-hosted runtime.
// stage0, stage1, and stage2 describe progressive compiler self-validation.
// self_compile marks the point where Norscode can compile its own runtime sources.
// runtime_image packages compiled modules with metadata for loading.

// Primitive flow:
// source_unit -> token_stream -> parser -> ast
// -> semantic_check -> lower_ast
// -> bytecode_builder -> bytecode_module
// -> link_module -> runtime_image
// -> image_loader -> execution_loop

// Bootstrap flow:
// seed_runtime -> stage0 compiler
// -> stage1 self_compile
// -> stage2 target_runtime
// -> runtime_image

