// Semantic direction:
// debugger gives a running VM an interactive inspection boundary.
// debug_session tracks one attached debug client and its active state.
// debug_target identifies the VM instance or thread under inspection.
// breakpoint marks an instruction address where execution should pause.
// breakpoint_set registers breakpoints keyed by breakpoint_id.
// conditional_break pauses only when a user predicate evaluates true.
// watchpoint triggers on mutation of a named value or address range.
// step_into descends into called functions, step_over skips them.
// step_out resumes until the current call_frame returns.
// call_frame captures one activation: locals, upvalues, and return address.
// stack_trace enumerates live call_frames from innermost to outermost.
// inspect_value reads a runtime value without disturbing execution state.
// source_map links instruction addresses back to source lines and columns.
// debug_info stores symbol names, type annotations, and scope boundaries.
// debug_event notifies listeners when breakpoints, watchpoints, or steps fire.

// Primitive flow:
// debugger + debug_target -> debug_session
// -> breakpoint_set + watchpoint
// -> execution_loop + instruction_pointer
// -> breakpoint_hit or watchpoint_trigger
// -> pause + stack_trace + inspect_value
// -> source_map -> source_line + debug_symbol
// -> debug_event -> event_listener
// -> step or continue_exec

// This extends the self-hosted runtime pipeline with practical debugger
// and execution inspection semantics.

