// Semantic direction:
// pipeline_stage describes one step in the compiler: parse, type_check, lower, codegen.
// typed_ast is the output of type_check_stage: an AST where every node carries a type.
// typed_node wraps an AST node with its inferred node_type and source node_span.
// typed_expr and typed_stmt are the typed versions of expression and statement nodes.
// type_lowering transforms typed_ast into typed_ir, preserving type annotations.
// erase_types strips type annotations from IR nodes for backends that don't need them.
// emit_type_metadata produces type_metadata records for runtime reflection.
// attach_type_ids assigns a type_id to each IR value for GC and debugger use.
// typed_ir_func holds a function body in IR form with type annotations on each value.
// typed_ir_instr carries the type of its result alongside the operation.
// type_driven_opt uses type information to improve optimizer decisions.
// type_guided_inline marks generic functions as inline candidates after monomorphization.
// type_guided_specialize generates type-specific fast paths for known numeric types.
// type_constant_fold evaluates expressions whose operand types have known constant values.
// incremental_typecheck caches the type results for unchanged modules.
// module_type_signature summarizes exported names and their types.
// signature_hash gives each module_type_signature a stable digest for change detection.
// invalidate_dependents re-checks modules whose imported types have changed.
// type_export makes type definitions visible across module boundaries.
// type_import brings foreign types into the current module's type_env.
// cross_module_type references a type defined in another module via its type_id.
// type_coverage measures the fraction of AST nodes with resolved types.
// untyped_nodes counts nodes that could not be resolved (useful for debugging inference).

// Primitive flow:
// source_unit -> parse_stage -> ast
// -> type_check_stage -> typed_ast + type_env + type_errors
// -> type_lowering -> typed_ir
// -> erase_types or emit_type_metadata (per target)
// -> lower_stage -> codegen_stage -> output

// Incremental path:
// signature_hash comparison -> invalidate_dependents
// -> typecheck_cache hit or re-check
// -> merge into typed_ast

// Optimization path:
// typed_ir + type_driven_opt
// -> type_guided_inline + type_guided_specialize + type_constant_fold

// This integrates the full type system into the Norscode compiler pipeline,
// connecting inference, checking, lowering, optimization, and incremental builds.

