}

// Semantic direction:
// wasm_module is the top-level container for a compiled Norscode program as WASM.
// wasm_section is one named segment of the binary; section_order must follow the spec.
// type_section records all func_types used in the module (deduplicated by signature).
// function_section maps func_index to type_index; code_section holds the bodies.
// import_section declares external functions, tables, memories, and globals.
// export_section makes module internals accessible to the host or other modules.
// memory_section declares linear memories with initial and optional maximum page counts.
// global_section declares module-level mutable or immutable values.
// element_section initializes table slots with func_indexes.
// data_section initializes memory regions with static byte content.
// custom_section carries non-functional data: names, source maps, debug info.
// func_type pairs param_types and result_types; WASM functions have exactly one result.
// type_index is the ordinal of a func_type in the type_section.
// wasm_import names an external symbol from import_module with an import_desc.
// wasm_export exposes an internal symbol under export_name for the host.
// global_init is a constant expression that sets the initial value of a wasm_global.
// magic_bytes is the four-byte WASM magic number (0x00 0x61 0x73 0x6D).
// leb128_encode serializes unsigned and signed integers in the WASM variable-length format.
// wasm_buffer accumulates the binary output of wasm_emit calls.

// Primitive flow:
// Norscode typed_ir -> wasm_module construction
// -> type_section: collect all func_types, assign type_index
// -> import_section: runtime and host imports
// -> function_section: func_index -> type_index mappings
// -> code_section: function bodies (z264)
// -> memory_section: linear memory declaration (z265)
// -> export_section: public symbols
// -> leb128_encode all integers -> wasm_bytes -> wasm_buffer
// -> magic_bytes + version_bytes + sections -> binary file

// This establishes the WASM binary module structure
// as the output format for the Norscode WASM backend.

