// Semantic direction:
// wasm_instr is one encoded instruction in a WASM function body.
// opcode is the single or multi-byte prefix that identifies an instruction.
// instr_immediate is the operand embedded in the instruction stream (label, index, offset).
// const_i32 and const_i64 push integer immediates; const_f64 pushes a float.
// Arithmetic instructions operate on the implicit value stack: two pops, one push.
// local_get pushes the value of a local variable; local_set pops and stores.
// local_tee stores and also leaves a copy on the stack (useful for chains).
// global_get and global_set read and write module-level wasm_globals.
// load_i32 reads four bytes from linear memory at a given address and offset.
// store_i32 writes a value from the stack into linear memory.
// load_offset and load_align are immediates that control address computation.
// call invokes a function by func_index; arguments are on the stack.
// call_indirect calls via a table entry, checking the func_type at runtime.
// block and loop_instr are structured control constructs that define br targets.
// br jumps to the enclosing block's end; in a loop, br jumps to its top.
// br_if pops a condition and jumps if non-zero.
// br_table implements a switch by indexing into a list of branch targets.
// if_instr pops a condition; the else_instr separates true and false branches.
// end_instr closes a block, loop, if, or function body.
// i32_wrap_i64 truncates i64 to i32; i64_extend_i32_s sign-extends i32 to i64.
// func_locals declares the set of local variable types before the instruction stream.

// Primitive flow:
// typed_ir_instr -> wasm_instr selection
// operands -> stack discipline verification
// local variables -> func_locals declaration + local_get/local_set
// memory access -> load/store + load_offset
// control flow -> block/loop/if + br/br_if/br_table
// function call -> call + type_index check
// numeric casts -> i32_wrap_i64 or i64_extend_i32_s etc.
// instr_encode -> opcode + immediates -> instr_buffer -> code_section

// This defines the WASM instruction selection and binary encoding layer
// that translates Norscode typed IR into executable WASM bytecode.

