// Semantic direction:
// linear_memory is the flat byte array that WASM programs use for all heap data.
// page_size is 65536 bytes; WASM memories are sized in pages.
// initial_pages declares how many pages are allocated at module startup.
// max_pages sets an optional ceiling; memory_grow requests additional pages at runtime.
// heap_layout partitions linear memory into fixed regions before runtime data.
// static_region holds data_segment content: string literals, constants, and type metadata.
// stack_region reserves space for a shadow stack used by multi-value returns and closures.
// heap_region is the area managed by bump_alloc for dynamic objects.
// bump_alloc advances heap_ptr by alloc_size rounded up to alloc_align.
// alloc_result is the base address of the newly allocated region.
// string_layout places a length word followed by UTF-8 bytes; string_ptr points to the base.
// string_alloc reserves space for a string in the heap region.
// list_layout places len, cap, and a data_ptr to the element array.
// list_grow reallocates the element array when cap is exceeded.
// struct_ptr is the base address of a struct in linear memory.
// field_load reads bytes at struct_ptr + field_byte_offset.
// field_store writes bytes at struct_ptr + field_byte_offset.
// rc_header is a reference-count word prepended to every heap-allocated object.
// rc_increment increases the count; rc_decrement decreases it and frees if zero.
// addr_i32 represents a memory address as a 32-bit WASM integer.
// data_segment initializes a region of linear memory at segment_offset with segment_bytes.
// memory_import allows the host to supply a shared linear_memory to the module.
// memory_export exposes the module's linear_memory to the host for interop.

// Primitive flow:
// module init: data_segment -> segment_bytes copied to static_region
// heap_base = end of static_region; heap_ptr = heap_base
// alloc: heap_ptr + alloc_size + align -> alloc_addr; heap_ptr advances
// string alloc: string_alloc -> string_ptr; bytes written at string_ptr + 4
// struct alloc: bump_alloc(struct_layout.size) -> struct_ptr
// list alloc: bump_alloc(list_layout.header_size) -> list_ptr; data_ptr -> element array
// rc_decrement -> if count == 0 -> rc_free (adds to free list or marks region available)
// memory_grow: call WASM memory.grow instruction -> new page range

// This defines the WASM linear memory layout, allocator, and object representation
// used by the Norscode WASM runtime.

