// Semantic direction:
// wasm_func pairs a func_type with a func_body and its func_locals declarations.
// func_prologue sets up local variables and shadow_stack frame on entry.
// func_epilogue restores the shadow_stack and returns results on exit.
// call_conv describes how arguments and results flow between caller and callee.
// arg_passing puts arguments onto the WASM value stack before a call instruction.
// result_passing leaves return values on the value stack after a call returns.
// stack_discipline ensures each basic block leaves the stack in a known state.
// multi_value_return allows a WASM function to return more than one value.
// closure pairs a func_index with a closure_env (pointer to captured variables).
// closure_ptr is the address of a closure object in linear_memory.
// closure_alloc allocates space for the closure header and captured variable slots.
// closure_call loads the func_index from closure_ptr and uses call_indirect.
// trampoline is a small generated function that loads the closure_env and jumps.
// indirect_call_table is the WASM table used for call_indirect dispatch.
// table_slot holds one func_index; table_assign writes it during module init.
// builtin_func is a runtime-provided function imported from the host.
// builtin_dispatch maps builtin names to runtime_import entries.
// tail_call_opt replaces a recursive tail call with a br to the function's loop top.
// return_call is the WASM proposal instruction for guaranteed tail calls.
// shadow_stack is a region in linear_memory used for stack frames that escape WASM's value stack.
// shadow_frame records locals that are address-taken or captured by closures.
// shadow_push allocates a new shadow_frame; shadow_pop restores the previous one.
// stack_overflow_check compares shadow_stack pointer against stack_limit.

// Primitive flow:
// Norscode func def -> wasm_func + func_type -> type_section + function_section
// param types -> local variables 0..n; additional locals -> func_locals
// function body -> func_prologue (shadow_push if needed)
// -> instruction stream
// -> func_epilogue (shadow_pop) + result_passing
// closure creation -> closure_alloc -> closure_ptr; env vars stored at offsets
// closure_call -> load func_index from closure_ptr -> call_indirect
// builtin call -> call runtime_import by builtin_index
// tail call -> tail_call_opt -> br 0 (loop top)

// This defines WASM function structure, calling conventions, closures,
// indirect dispatch, and shadow stack semantics for the Norscode WASM backend.

