// Semantic direction:
// host_env is the JavaScript or WASI environment that embeds the WASM module.
// host_func is a function provided by the host and imported into the module.
// host_import names a host_func in the import_section under a module namespace.
// host_export makes a Norscode function callable from host_env.
// js_value is the type-erased representation of any JavaScript value at the boundary.
// extern_ref is the WASM opaque reference type used to hold host_objects.
// extern_ref_table is a WASM table of extern_refs for host object handles.
// extern_ref_get fetches a host_object from extern_ref_table by index.
// extern_ref_set stores a new host_object into a table slot.
// marshal_to_js converts Norscode values to representations the host can consume.
// marshal_from_js converts host-supplied values into Norscode's linear memory layout.
// coerce_js_string reads a JavaScript string into a Norscode string in linear memory.
// coerce_js_number reads a JavaScript number as a Norscode float or integer.
// wasm_bindgen is the code generation step that produces glue for each exported function.
// export_attr marks a Norscode function as visible to the host with a given name.
// ts_decl generates TypeScript type declarations for exported symbols.
// dom_api is the set of browser DOM functions available via host_import.
// console_log and console_error are imported host functions for debug output.
// fetch_api provides HTTP access via the browser Fetch API.
// promise is the host representation of an asynchronous result.
// async_bridge connects Norscode's async/await model to JavaScript Promises.

