// Semantic direction:
// wasi is the WebAssembly System Interface: a standard ABI for system calls in WASM.
// wasi_snapshot_preview1 is the stable version of WASI used by most current toolchains.
// wasi_import declares each WASI function as a host_import under the "wasi_snapshot_preview1" namespace.
// fd_read reads bytes from a file descriptor into iovec buffers.
// fd_write writes bytes from ciovec buffers to a file descriptor.
// fd_seek repositions the file offset; fd_tell returns the current offset.
// fd_prestat_get returns metadata about a preopened_dir associated with a fd.
// fd_prestat_dir_name copies the path name of a preopened_dir into a buffer.
// path_open opens or creates a file relative to a directory file descriptor.
// path_stat queries metadata for a path without opening it.
// args_get copies command-line argument strings into linear memory.
// args_sizes_get returns the count and total byte size of all arguments.
// environ_get copies environment variable strings into linear memory.
// clock_time_get reads the current time from a named clock.
// clock_realtime is the wall clock; clock_monotonic never goes backwards.
// proc_exit terminates the WASM instance with a numeric exit code.
// random_get fills a buffer with cryptographically random bytes.
// poll_oneoff blocks until one or more subscriptions become ready.
// iovec describes a memory buffer region for scatter-gather I/O.
// wasi_rights is a bitfield controlling which operations are allowed on a fd.
// preopened_dir is a directory the host grants access to at module startup.
// wasi_errno is the numeric result code returned by most WASI calls.
// errno_success is zero; other values indicate failure categories.

// Primitive flow:
// Norscode I/O -> WASI import call
// fd_write: format iovec (ptr + len) in linear memory -> call fd_write import
// fd_read: allocate buffer in linear memory -> call fd_read -> read iovec
// path_open: preopened_dir fd + relative path -> new fd
// clock_time_get: clock_id -> nanosecond timestamp in linear memory
// args_get: args_sizes_get -> alloc buffers -> args_get fills them
// proc_exit: call with integer code -> module terminates
// random_get: alloc buffer -> call -> buffer filled with random bytes

// Startup path:
// module init -> fd_prestat_get on fd 3, 4, ... until errno_badf
// -> collect preopened_dirs for path_open calls

// This defines the WASI system interface imported by Norscode WASM modules
// for file I/O, arguments, environment, clocks, and process control.

