// Semantic direction:
// document_store maps document_uri to document_entry, keeping the live text for each open file.
// document_version increments on each did_change notification, tracking edit sequences.
// sync_incremental allows the client to send only changed text_edit ranges.
// sync_full requires the client to resend the entire document_text on each change.
// did_open adds a new document_entry; did_close removes it from document_store.
// did_change applies one or more text_edits to the stored document_text.
// text_edit describes one replacement: edit_range (start/end positions) and edit_new_text.
// position uses line and utf16 character offset, matching the LSP specification.
// line_index is a precomputed array of byte offsets for the start of each line.
// build_line_index scans the document_text once and records every newline position.
// offset_to_position converts a byte offset to a line/character position using line_index.
// position_to_offset converts an LSP position back to a byte offset for compiler use.
// utf16_offset translates between UTF-16 character counts (LSP) and byte offsets (compiler).
// apply_edit mutates document_text and rebuilds line_index for the changed region.
// parse_document runs lexer and parser over the current document_text.
// parse_result bundles the parse_ast, parse_errors, and parse_tokens for this version.
// reparse_debounce waits reparse_delay milliseconds after the last edit before parsing.
// document_snapshot captures a stable view of ast, tokens, and errors at a given version.
// doc_cache stores snapshots to avoid redundant parses when version has not changed.
// invalidate_doc evicts the cached snapshot when a did_change arrives.

// Primitive flow:
// did_open -> document_store.insert(uri, text) -> build_line_index -> parse_document
// did_change -> apply_edit(text_edits) -> update line_index -> reparse_debounce
// reparse_debounce fires -> parse_document -> document_snapshot stored
// did_close -> document_store.remove(uri) -> invalidate_doc
// request arrives for uri -> doc_cache lookup -> snapshot_ast available
// position in request -> position_to_offset -> byte offset for compiler queries

// This defines LSP document lifecycle, incremental text editing,
// line index management, and debounced parsing for the Norscode language server.

