// Semantic direction:
// definition_request is sent when the user invokes go-to-definition on a symbol.
// definition_params carries the document_uri and cursor definition_position.
// definition_response returns one or more definition_locations, or definition_null.
// definition_location is a target_uri and target_range pointing to the declaration site.
// definition_link adds origin_selection_range (the reference site) and target_selection_range (the name token).
// declaration_request jumps to the forward declaration; type_definition_request jumps to the type.
// references_request finds all uses of the symbol across the workspace.
// include_declaration controls whether the declaration itself appears in reference_list.
// symbol_entry records one declaration: name, kind, defined_at, type, and owning module.
// symbol_table maps names to symbol_entries within a module scope.
// resolve_at_position finds the symbol_entry for the identifier token at the cursor position.
// resolve_ident looks up a bare name in the current scope chain.
// resolve_field resolves field_name on a struct type using the type_repr of the receiver.
// resolve_method resolves a method call on a struct or union type.
// resolve_import follows an import statement to its source module_uri.
// definition_index caches symbol locations per file for fast cross-file lookup.
// index_by_position maps byte offsets to symbol_entries for O(log n) resolution.
// cross_file_resolve follows import_graph edges to find definitions in other files.
// find_module_file maps a module name to its file path using the project's norcode.toml.
// workspace_symbol responds to a fuzzy query over all indexed symbols in the workspace.
// fuzzy_match ranks symbol names by edit distance or substring match against symbol_query.
// symbol_kind classifies symbols: function, struct, union, variable, field, module, variant.

