// Semantic direction:
// version is a structured SemVer triple: ver_major.ver_minor.ver_patch with optional pre and build.
// pre_release_id is a dot-separated list of alphanumeric identifiers (e.g. "alpha.1").
// build_metadata is additional label information that does not affect precedence.
// version_compare implements SemVer precedence: major > minor > patch > pre-release ordering.
// pre_release_order: numeric identifiers sort numerically; alphanumeric sort lexicographically.
// version_req is a constraint expression that a version must satisfy.
// op_caret (^1.2.3) allows changes that do not modify the leftmost non-zero digit.
// op_tilde (~1.2.3) allows patch-level changes when minor is specified.
// op_wildcard (1.*) matches any value in the wildcard position.
// caret_rule: ^1.2.3 means >=1.2.3, <2.0.0; ^0.2.3 means >=0.2.3, <0.3.0.
// tilde_rule: ~1.2.3 means >=1.2.3, <1.3.0.
// req_matches checks whether a version satisfies a version_req.
// req_and combines two requirements: both must be satisfied.
// filter_by_req removes versions from version_candidates that do not satisfy version_req.
// select_best picks the highest version from the filtered set.
// latest_compatible returns the newest version satisfying all constraints.
// breaking_major is a change that increments ver_major (incompatible API change).
// breaking_minor_zero applies to 0.x versions where minor bumps may break.
// compatible_release is a change that only increments ver_minor (new features, backward compatible).
// patch_release is a change that only increments ver_patch (bug fixes).
// bump_major increments ver_major and resets minor and patch to zero.
// next_version produces the next version according to a specified bump kind.

// Primitive flow:
// version_parse("1.2.3-alpha.1+build.42") -> version struct
// version_req parse("^1.2.3") -> req_comparator with op_caret + version
// req_matches(v, req) -> caret_rule(v, req_version) -> bool
// resolution: version_candidates list -> filter_by_req -> select_best
// bump: current_version + bump_kind -> next_version

// This defines SemVer parsing, comparison, requirement matching,
// and version selection semantics for the Norscode package manager.

