// Semantic direction:
// fetch_command is the nc hent implementation: resolves, downloads, verifies, and caches.
// fetch_all downloads every package in the resolved lockfile, preparing for an offline build.
// fetch_offline uses only the local package_cache and fails if any package is missing.
// download_manager coordinates parallel downloads with a bounded download_concurrency.
// download_job carries the url, destination path, and expected checksum for one archive.
// download_progress tracks bytes received versus total for display in the terminal.
// parallel_download launches multiple download_jobs concurrently and waits for all to complete.
// archive_tar_gz is the primary distribution format: a gzipped tar archive.
// extract_archive unpacks the downloaded archive into extract_dest.
// extract_strip_prefix removes the top-level directory from the archive path.
// package_cache stores downloaded and extracted archives on the local filesystem.
// cache_dir is the root directory for all cached packages (e.g. ~/.cache/norscode/packages/).
// cache_key is derived from package_name + version + source_url + checksum.
// cache_lock prevents concurrent processes from writing the same cache_entry simultaneously.
// cache_evict removes entries when cache_size_limit is approached, keeping most-recently-used entries.
// verify_download recomputes the archive checksum and compares it to locked_checksum.
// verify_signature checks a cryptographic signature from the publisher against signature_pubkey.
// source_tree is the extracted package directory ready for compilation.
// registry_token is the authentication token read from token_path or token_env_override.
// token_store writes a new token to token_path with restricted file permissions.
// fetch_summary reports how many packages were downloaded, served from cache, and verified.

// Primitive flow:
// nc hent -> lockfile_parse -> download_queue (packages not yet in cache)
// -> download_manager:
//    for each download_job in parallel:
//      http_get download_url -> download_bytes
//      -> download_progress display
//      -> verify_download: recompute checksum -> verify_ok or verify_fail
//      -> verify_fail: delete archive + error
//      -> extract_archive -> source_tree
//      -> cache_entry written
// fetch_all: process entire lockfile
// fetch_offline: cache_hit check only -> abort on cache_miss
// -> fetch_summary printed

// This defines the nc hent download pipeline: parallel fetching, archive
// extraction, checksum verification, and local package caching.

