// Semantic direction:
// publish_command implements nc publiser: packages, signs, and uploads a new version.
// publish_dry_run performs all steps except the final HTTP upload, for pre-flight checking.
// publish_allow_dirty bypasses the clean git working tree check (useful in CI).
// package_builder collects the files to include in the distribution archive.
// include_glob and exclude_glob patterns filter which files are packaged.
// build_source_list walks the project directory and applies include/exclude filters.
// archive_builder writes a tar.gz archive from the collected file_entries.
// archive_checksum is the SHA-256 of the finished archive, written to the lockfile.
// package_signer signs the archive with the author's signing_key.
// ed25519_sign produces a 64-byte signature over the archive_checksum.
// signing_key_path reads the private key from a file; signing_key_env reads from an env variable.
// publish_metadata assembles the JSON body from the project manifest fields.
// publish_readme_content reads the readme file and attaches it to the metadata.
// publish_links is a set of named URLs (docs, source, issues) added to the registry listing.
// publish_form encodes the request as multipart: form_metadata JSON + form_archive bytes + form_signature.
// publish_conflict is returned when the version is already present in the registry.
// pre_publish_check runs a series of validations before any upload is attempted.
// check_version_new verifies the version does not already exist in the registry index.
// check_no_dirty_git aborts if uncommitted changes are present (unless publish_allow_dirty).
// check_license_present ensures the manifest declares a license.
// version_bump_command increments the version in norcode.toml and creates a git tag.
// bump_and_tag commits the version change and pushes the tag to the remote.

// Primitive flow:
// nc publiser -> pre_publish_check:
//   check_manifest_valid + check_license_present
//   + check_readme_exists + check_no_dirty_git + check_version_new
// -> build_source_list (include_glob / exclude_glob)
// -> archive_builder -> archive_bytes + archive_checksum
// -> package_signer -> ed25519_sign(archive_checksum) -> signature_bytes
// -> publish_metadata (from manifest fields + readme_content)
// -> publish_form: multipart(metadata JSON, archive bytes, signature)
// -> http_post registry_url/publish -> publish_response
// -> publish_ok: print confirmation + version URL
// -> publish_conflict: "versjon finnes allerede" error
// dry_run: stop before http_post, print summary

// This defines the nc publiser pipeline: source collection, archive building,
// cryptographic signing, pre-flight checks, and registry upload.

