// Semantic direction:
// registry_server is a self-hosted package registry compatible with the Norscode registry protocol.
// server_config loads host, port, TLS, storage backend, and database settings.
// storage_filesystem stores archives in a local directory tree.
// storage_s3 delegates to an S3-compatible object store (AWS, MinIO, R2).
// storage_url returns the download URL for an archived package version.
// registry_db persists package metadata, user accounts, tokens, and ownership records.
// db_migrate applies schema updates to an existing database on startup.
// auth_system validates API tokens on every authenticated request.
// api_token is a long-lived credential issued at token_create.
// scope_publish allows uploading new versions; scope_yank allows marking versions unsafe.
// scope_manage_owners allows adding and removing co-owners of a package.
// owner_record ties a user_account to a package name; only owners may publish or yank.
// mirror is a read-only proxy that caches packages from an upstream registry.
// mirror_sync periodically fetches the upstream index to keep the local mirror current.
// mirror_proxy forwards download requests to upstream when the local cache is cold.
// proxy_cache_hit serves the archive from local storage; proxy_cache_miss fetches from mirror_upstream.
// mirror_sync_interval controls how often the index is refreshed from upstream.
// rate_limiter throttles requests per IP or token to protect the server under load.
// rate_limit_key identifies the subject being rate-limited (IP or token_id).
// rate_exceeded returns a response_rate_limited response and includes a retry-after header.
// server_metrics records counters for downloads, uploads, searches, and active users.

// Primitive flow:
// server startup: load server_config -> db_migrate -> storage_backend init -> server_listen
// publish request: auth_system(token) -> scope_publish -> owner check
//   -> storage_write(archive) -> db_versions insert -> index update
// download request: db_versions lookup -> storage_url -> redirect or proxy
// mirror sync: mirror_sync_interval tick -> fetch upstream index -> update local db_packages
// mirror proxy: request arrives -> local storage_read -> hit: serve; miss: proxy_fetch_upstream
// rate_limiter: per request -> rate_limit_key check -> count in rate_window
//   -> rate_exceeded -> response_rate_limited

// This defines the private registry server, S3-backed storage, auth system,
// ownership model, and mirroring semantics for self-hosted Norscode registries.

