// Semantic direction:
// workflow is a YAML file in .github/workflows/ that defines automated CI/CD processes.
// workflow_on declares which events trigger the workflow.
// trigger_push fires on commits pushed to matching branches or tags.
// trigger_pull_request fires when a PR is opened, synchronized, or reopened.
// trigger_schedule uses cron syntax to fire on a time interval.
// trigger_workflow_dispatch allows manual triggering with optional inputs.
// trigger_workflow_call makes the workflow reusable by other workflows.
// branch_filter limits push or PR triggers to specific branch name patterns.
// path_filter limits triggers to changes under specific directory paths.
// workflow_concurrency cancels in-progress runs when a new one starts for the same group.
// job groups related steps into one unit executed on a single runner.
// job_runs_on selects the runner type: ubuntu, macos, windows, or a self_hosted label.
// job_needs expresses a dependency on another job completing successfully first.
// job_strategy with job_matrix generates parallel job instances for each matrix combination.
// job_fail_fast stops all matrix siblings when one instance fails.
// step is one command or action within a job; steps run sequentially.
// step_uses references a reusable GitHub Action by its repository path and version.
// step_run executes a shell command directly on the runner.
// step_if evaluates a condition expression; the step is skipped when false.
// github_token is the auto-provisioned credential for API calls within a workflow run.
// github_context provides runtime values: commit SHA, branch ref, and triggering event.

// Primitive flow:
// git push -> trigger_push -> branch_filter check
// -> workflow starts -> job_needs graph resolved
// -> for each job: runner_allocated -> steps execute sequentially
// -> matrix: N runner instances in parallel, one per matrix combination
// -> job_outputs collected -> downstream jobs consume via needs context
// -> workflow success/failure reported to GitHub commit status

// This establishes the GitHub Actions workflow structure and job model
// as the foundation of the Norscode CI/CD automation system.

