// Semantic direction:
// release_workflow triggers when a semver_tag (e.g. v1.2.3) is pushed to the repository.
// tag_pattern matches tags of the form v[0-9]+.[0-9]+.[0-9]+ with optional pre-release suffix.
// release_job_validate checks that the tag version matches the manifest and changelog.
// tag_version parses the version number from the pushed tag name.
// manifest_version reads the version from norcode.toml.
// version_match_check fails the release if tag_version differs from manifest_version.
// changelog_entry_check verifies that CHANGELOG.md contains a section for this version.
// no_pre_release_deps fails if any dependency in the lockfile is a pre-release version.
// build_matrix generates one binary per target platform in parallel.
// binary_artifact is the compiled nc executable for one platform.
// artifact_upload stores a binary_artifact in the GitHub workflow artifact store.
// artifact_download retrieves platform binaries in the release assembly job.
// release_package bundles a binary with the stdlib and install script for distribution.
// package_name_pattern is a template like "norscode-{version}-{platform}.tar.gz".
// release_manifest is a JSON file listing all release assets with their checksums.
// github_release creates the GitHub Release record under the pushed tag.
// release_body is populated from extract_changelog_entry for the released version.
// release_draft allows human review before the release is made public.
// release_prerelease marks alpha/beta/rc tags as pre-releases in the GitHub UI.
// asset_upload attaches each platform package to the github_release.
// release_notes is the formatted markdown shown on the GitHub Release page.
// release_notify sends announcements to configured channels after a successful release.

// Primitive flow:
// git tag v1.2.3 && git push --tags
// -> release_workflow trigger
// -> release_job_validate:
//    tag_version(v1.2.3) == manifest_version? fail if not
//    changelog_entry_check -> CHANGELOG.md has "## 1.2.3" section?
//    no_pre_release_deps check
// -> build_matrix (parallel per platform) -> binary_artifact -> artifact_upload
// -> release_job_package: artifact_download all -> release_package per platform
//    -> asset_upload to github_release
// -> release_job_publish_registry: nc publiser -> registry
// -> release_job_create_release: extract_changelog_entry -> release_body -> github_release publish
// -> release_job_notify: announcement to configured channels

// This defines the release pipeline from version tag push to published
// GitHub Release with all platform artifacts.

