// Semantic direction:
// nightly_workflow runs on a fixed nightly_cron schedule (e.g. 02:00 UTC every day).
// nightly_version embeds the date and commit SHA: e.g. 0.0.0-nightly.2026-05-28+abc1234.
// nightly_build_id combines date and commit for unique identification.
// nightly_job_prune removes old nightly builds beyond max_nightly_builds or prune_older_than.
// prune_keep_tagged preserves any nightly that was explicitly tagged or bookmarked.
// pre_release is a version with a pre_release_kind suffix: alpha, beta, or rc.
// pre_release_number increments within one kind: 1.2.0-beta.1, 1.2.0-beta.2, etc.
// pre_release_workflow triggers when a pre_release_tag (e.g. v1.2.0-beta.1) is pushed.
// pre_release_validation runs the same checks as the release pipeline but marks it pre-release.
// channel_manifest lists versions for each channel with download URLs and checksums.
// channel_update publishes new entries to the manifest as builds complete.
// switch_channel lets a user move their nc installation from stable to beta or nightly.
// pin_version locks a specific version, preventing automatic updates.
// nightly_test_suite extends the normal test run with slow, expensive, or fuzzing tests.
// fuzz_run executes a fuzz harness for a fixed fuzz_duration to discover crashes.
// fuzz_corpus is the saved set of interesting inputs for the fuzzer.
// fuzz_crash is saved and filed as a bug when the fuzzer finds a panic or assertion failure.
// fuzz_minimize reduces a fuzz_crash input to its smallest reproducing form.
// nightly_diff shows what changed since the previous nightly for the release notes.
// nightly_report summarizes test results, binary size, and benchmark performance.

// Primitive flow:
// cron fires at nightly_cron time -> nightly_workflow
// -> checkout HEAD of nightly_branch -> nightly_version from date + sha
// -> nightly_job_build: cross-platform matrix (same as release)
// -> nightly_job_test: normal suite + extended_test + fuzz_run(fuzz_duration)
//    -> fuzz_crash detected? -> fuzz_minimize -> file issue + fail nightly
// -> nightly_job_publish: upload to channel_nightly -> channel_update
// -> nightly_job_prune: remove builds beyond max_nightly_builds
// -> nightly_job_notify: nightly_report -> post to dev channel
// pre_release tag push -> pre_release_workflow:
//   same as release but gh_release with release_prerelease=true
//   -> channel_rc or channel_beta updated
// nc update --channel nightly: switch_channel -> channel_manifest -> download_update

// This defines nightly build scheduling, pre-release channels, fuzzing,
// channel manifests, and version pinning for the Norscode distribution system.

