}

// Semantic direction:
// security_workflow runs on push, PR, and a weekly scan_schedule.
// sast (Static Application Security Testing) analyzes source code for vulnerability patterns.
// sast_ruleset contains the active set of security rules for Norscode code.
// sast_finding reports one potential issue: rule, severity, location, and CWE category.
// sarif_output is the standard SARIF JSON format for security finding interchange.
// upload_sarif posts the SARIF file to GitHub's Code Scanning UI.
// dependency_scan checks every locked package against the advisory_database.
// dep_vulnerability links a specific package version to a known CVE or advisory.
// vuln_patched_version is the earliest version that resolves the vulnerability.
// advisory_database is updated from osv.dev or a Norscode-maintained registry.
// audit_fix automatically upgrades a vulnerable package to its audit_fix_version.
// auto_update_patch applies compatible patch-level upgrades for vulnerability fixes.
// secret_scanner detects accidentally committed credentials using secret_pattern regexes.
// secret_finding reports the type, file path, and a secret_value_masked preview.
// allowed_patterns lists known-safe strings that would otherwise trigger false positives.
// sbom (Software Bill of Materials) enumerates all components and their licenses.
// sbom_spdx and sbom_cyclonedx are the two standard SBOM interchange formats.
// sbom_component records name, version, license, and content hash for one dependency.
// sbom_attest signs the SBOM with a Sigstore attestation for supply chain verification.
// dependabot_config configures GitHub Dependabot to open automated PRs for outdated packages.
// dependabot_schedule controls check frequency (daily, weekly, monthly).
// dependabot_open_pr is the maximum number of open Dependabot PRs at one time.

// Primitive flow:
// push/PR: secret_scanner -> secret_finding? -> block merge + alert owner
// push/PR: sast -> sast_findings -> sarif_output -> upload_sarif -> Code Scanning annotations
// weekly: advisory_db_update -> dependency_scan over lockfile
//   -> vuln found? -> audit_result with severity
//   -> high severity: fail CI + open issue
//   -> auto_update_patch: update lockfile to patched version + open PR
// release: sbom_generate -> sbom_spdx + sbom_cyclonedx -> sbom_attest -> attached to release
// dependabot: weekly check norcode packages -> dependabot_open_pr for outdated deps

// This defines security scanning, dependency vulnerability management,
// secret detection, SBOM generation, and Dependabot integration.

