  write_output
  build_sitemap
  build_feed
  build_search_index

  dev_server
  dev_watch
  dev_reload
  dev_port
}

// Semantic direction:
// site_builder is the top-level orchestrator that produces a complete static website.
// site_config is loaded from a TOML or Norscode config file at the project root.
// site_base_url is the canonical URL prefix used for all absolute links in the output.
// page is one output HTML file with its source content, metadata, and navigation pointers.
// page_toc is the auto-generated table of contents derived from heading structure.
// page_prev and page_next link adjacent pages within the same section for navigation.
// page_edit_url links to the source file on GitHub for community contribution.
// section groups related pages into a navigable hierarchy.
// section_weight controls the display order of sections in the navigation sidebar.
// template_engine processes template_files with a context object to produce HTML.
// template_extend implements template inheritance: a page template fills blocks defined in a base.
// template_include inlines a partial template at the call site.
// markdown_parser converts source markdown to HTML, respecting Norscode code fence syntax.
// frontmatter is TOML metadata at the top of each markdown file (title, weight, draft).
// frontmatter_draft excludes a page from the built site while still processing it locally.
// asset_fingerprint appends a content hash to asset filenames for cache-busting.
// asset_minify_css and asset_minify_js reduce file sizes for production output.
// build_sitemap generates sitemap.xml listing all public pages with last_modified dates.
// build_feed produces an Atom or RSS feed for the changelog or blog section.
// build_search_index creates a JSON index consumed by the client-side search engine (z308).
// dev_server serves the built site locally with dev_watch for hot dev_reload on changes.

// Primitive flow:
// site_config load -> site_build_dir clean
// collect_content: walk site_content_dir -> parse frontmatter + markdown_source per page
// collect_assets: copy site_static_dir -> asset_fingerprint
// render_pages: for each page -> template_render(template_context) -> HTML string
// write_output: HTML strings + assets -> site_build_dir
// build_sitemap -> sitemap.xml; build_feed -> feed.xml; build_search_index -> search.json
// dev_server: serve site_build_dir on dev_port; dev_watch -> rebuild on change -> dev_reload

// This establishes the static site generator core and build pipeline
// used to produce the Norscode documentation website.

