}

// Semantic direction:
// lang_ref_builder generates the full language reference section of the documentation site.
// syntax_ref enumerates every keyword with its description and usage examples.
// keyword_entry documents one reserved word: its meaning, syntax context, and related keywords.
// keyword_example is a complete, runnable code snippet illustrating the keyword's use.
// operator_ref lists all operators with precedence, associativity, and description.
// operator_precedence is the binding strength used to order operations without parentheses.
// type_ref covers every built-in type: heltall, desimaltall, tekst, boolsk, liste, ordbok, valgfri.
// type_operations lists the methods and operators applicable to each type.
// type_conversions documents safe and lossy conversions between types.
// statement_ref documents every statement form with syntax diagrams and error conditions.
// stmt_syntax is a formal EBNF-like notation showing the allowed structure.
// stmt_errors lists the compile-time errors that arise from misuse.
// control_flow_ref covers hvis/ellers, mens, for, bryt, fortsett, returner, prøv/fang/kast.
// declaration_ref documents funksjon, la, konstant, struktur, type aliases, and modul.
// grammar_rule is a formal production rule in the Norscode grammar.
// grammar_ebnf is the Extended Backus-Naur Form notation used for the grammar reference.
// grammar_diagram is a railroad diagram SVG generated from grammar_ebnf.
// example_snippet is a short, self-contained code sample with expected snippet_output.
// snippet_runnable marks examples that can be executed in the interactive playground.
// cross_ref links from one reference entry to related concepts in other sections.

// Primitive flow:
// lang_ref_builder invoked as part of site_builder
// -> all_keywords list -> per keyword: keyword_entry -> render page
// -> all_operators list -> per operator: operator_ref -> render page
// -> builtin_type list -> per type: type_ref page with type_operations + type_examples
// -> control_flow_ref: one page per construct with stmt_syntax + stmt_examples
// -> grammar_rule list -> grammar_ebnf -> grammar_diagram SVG
// -> example_snippets -> snippet_highlight (syntax coloring) + snippet_runnable marker
// -> cross_ref links woven between pages
// -> output: /referanse/ section of documentation site

// This defines the auto-generated language reference that documents every
// keyword, operator, type, statement, and grammar rule in Norscode.

