// Semantic direction:
// versioned_docs maintains separate documentation builds for each released version.
// doc_version maps to one git tag; the docs are built from that tag's source.
// version_label is the human-readable string shown in the version switcher (e.g. "v1.2" or "Nightly").
// version_stable is the most recent stable release; version_latest may be an RC or nightly.
// version_status classifies each version: current (actively maintained), legacy (security only), or unreleased.
// version_switcher is the UI component that lets readers move between versions on any page.
// version_redirect sends a browser from /docs/ to /docs/v1.2/ based on version_manifest.
// version_url_prefix is the path segment used to isolate one version (e.g. /docs/v1.2/).
// version_build checks out the version_source_tag and runs the site_builder for that snapshot.
// version_deploy_path is the subdirectory where the built version is published on the server.
// version_archive removes old builds beyond archive_policy (keep_n_versions or keep_major_versions).
// version_diff shows what changed in the documentation between two releases.
// canonical_url points to the current stable version to avoid duplicate-content penalties.
// noindex_old_versions adds a robots noindex directive to legacy doc versions.
// migration_guide documents breaking changes and how to update code between versions.
// migration_change_entry describes one breaking change with before/after code examples.
// change_category classifies the change: syntax, stdlib, compiler behavior, or CLI.
// deprecation_notice is a banner added to documentation pages for symbols marked deprecated.
// deprecated_since records which version introduced the deprecation.
// removed_in is the version where the deprecated symbol will be deleted.
// replacement links to the recommended alternative.
// version_ci builds and deploys docs for every release tag and updates version_manifest.

// Primitive flow:
// release tag pushed -> version_ci trigger:
//   version_checkout(tag) -> version_build -> version_deploy_path
//   -> update_version_manifest: add version_manifest_entry with url + label + status
// version_switcher: load version_manifest -> version_dropdown -> user selects version
//   -> navigate to version_url_prefix + current_page_path
// canonical_url: all version pages -> link rel=canonical -> stable version URL
// migration_guide: built from CHANGELOG.md breaking change entries + manual migration_steps
// archive: on new release -> archive_policy -> remove versions beyond threshold
// deprecation_notice: symbol has doc_deprecated_tag -> insert notice_banner into rendered page

// This defines versioned documentation builds, multi-version navigation,
// migration guides, deprecation notices, and archive policies.

