  crdt_merge
  crdt_delta
  eventual_consistency
}

// Semantic direction:
// consensus ensures that a cluster of nodes agrees on a sequence of state changes.
// raft_node participates in the Raft consensus protocol as leader, follower, or candidate.
// raft_term is a monotonically increasing epoch; a new term begins with each election.
// raft_log is the ordered sequence of log_entries; commit_index marks the last committed entry.
// last_applied is the index up to which log_entries have been applied to the state_machine.
// election_timeout fires when a follower does not receive a heartbeat; it starts a leader_election.
// start_election increments current_term, votes for self, and sends request_vote_rpc to all nodes.
// quorum is the minimum number of nodes that must agree for a decision to be durable.
// majority is ceil((cluster_size + 1) / 2); the Raft quorum is majority.
// replicate_entry sends append_entries RPCs to all followers; commit_if_majority advances commit_index.
// match_index tracks how far each follower's log matches the leader's; next_index is what to send next.
// apply_to_state_machine executes committed commands in log order.
// sm_snapshot captures the full state_machine state to truncate the log.
// distributed_kv is a strongly-consistent key-value store built on the Raft state_machine.
// kv_watch subscribes to changes on a key; kv_watch_prefix monitors a key namespace.
// kv_lease is a time-bounded grant; operations tied to a lease expire when lease_ttl elapses.
// distributed_lock uses a kv_lease with a leader-unique lease_holder to serialize access.
// lock_fencing_token is a monotonically increasing number preventing stale lock holders from writing.
// crdt (Conflict-free Replicated Data Type) provides eventual_consistency without coordination.
// crdt_merge combines two diverged replicas deterministically into a single converged state.
// crdt_delta sends only the change since the last merge rather than the full state.

// Primitive flow:
// startup: all nodes start as follower -> election_timeout fires on one node
// -> start_election -> request_vote_rpc to peers -> count_votes
// -> quorum achieved: become leader -> send heartbeats to suppress further elections
// client write: leader receives sm_command -> append to raft_log
//   -> replicate_entry to followers -> follower_ack when stored
//   -> commit_if_majority -> apply_to_state_machine -> respond to client
// client read (linearizable): leader verifies still leader via heartbeat quorum -> sm_query
// snapshot: sm_snapshot -> store -> truncate old log entries
// distributed_lock: kv_put(lock_key, holder, lease_ttl) via Raft -> if key absent: acquired
//   -> lock_fencing_token increments per acquisition -> stale holders rejected

// This defines the Raft consensus algorithm, distributed key-value store,
// distributed locks, and CRDTs for eventual consistency.

