// Semantic direction:
// llm_client is the Norscode interface to large language model APIs.
// llm_provider selects the backend: Anthropic, OpenAI (GPT), Mistral, or a local Ollama server.
// provider_norscode_local calls a model running inside the Norscode inference runtime (z333).
// message is one turn in a conversation: a role and content pair.
// role_system sets the model's behavior for the entire conversation.
// role_tool carries the result of a tool invocation back to the model.
// content_image attaches a base64-encoded or URL-referenced image for vision models.
// content_tool_use is the model's request to call a specific tool with arguments.
// content_tool_result is the application's response to a tool_use request.
// conversation_history is the ordered list of messages sent to the model.
// trim_history removes old messages when the conversation exceeds history_token_budget.
// prompt_template is a parameterized string with template_variables filled at render time.
// prompt_registry stores versioned prompts by name for consistent retrieval.
// prompt_version enables A/B testing and gradual rollout of improved prompts.
// completion_request is the full API call payload; temperature controls output randomness.
// request_top_p and request_top_k apply nucleus and top-k sampling.
// stop_sequences terminate generation early when the model produces a specific string.
// usage records input_tokens and output_tokens consumed, enabling cost tracking.
// cache_read_tokens are tokens served from the prompt cache at reduced cost.
// prompt_cache marks a portion of the system prompt as cacheable across requests.
// cache_control_persistent caches content across API sessions.
// count_tokens estimates token usage for a message list without sending an API request.
// truncate_to_budget removes messages from the oldest end until the budget is satisfied.

// Primitive flow:
// prompt_template.render({variable: value}) -> prompt string
// conversation.add_message(role_user, prompt) -> conversation_history
// token_budget_check: count_tokens(history) > budget -> trim_history
// completion_request: model, messages, max_tokens, temperature, tools
// -> llm_provider.complete(request) -> completion_response
// -> response_content (text) or content_tool_use (tool call)
// -> add response to conversation_history
// prompt_cache: system prompt with cache_control_persistent
//   -> cache_write_tokens on first call, cache_read_tokens on subsequent

// This defines the LLM client, multi-provider support, prompt templating,
// conversation management, and prompt caching for Norscode AI applications.

