}

// Semantic direction:
// embedding converts discrete data (text, code, images) into dense float vectors where similar items are geometrically close.
// model_text_embedding produces embeddings optimized for semantic text similarity.
// model_code_embedding produces embeddings tuned for code search and clone detection.
// normalize_embedding scales the vector to unit length so cosine_similarity equals dot_product.
// embed_texts batches multiple inputs in one request to improve throughput.
// cosine_similarity is the dot product of two unit vectors: 1.0 means identical direction.
// euclidean_distance is the straight-line distance; smaller means more similar.
// similarity_threshold is the minimum score for two items to be considered semantically related.
// most_similar returns the item with the highest similarity_score to a query.
// semantic_cluster groups embeddings by proximity using a cluster_algorithm.
// algo_kmeans partitions into a fixed cluster_count; inertia measures within-cluster variance.
// silhouette_score measures how well-separated clusters are; higher is better.
// dimensionality_reduction projects high-dimensional embeddings to 2D or 3D for visualization.
// method_umap preserves local and global structure better than method_tsne for large datasets.
// explained_variance (PCA) shows how much information is retained after reduction.
// semantic_dedup removes near-duplicate documents from a corpus using embedding similarity.
// dedup_threshold is the similarity_score above which two documents are considered duplicates.
// canonical_doc is the representative document kept from each dedup_group.
// cross_lingual embeddings place text from different languages in the same vector space.
// multilingual_model supports many languages simultaneously with shared representations.
// align_embeddings maps monolingual embedding spaces to a common multilingual space.
// fine_tune_embeddings adapts a pre-trained model to a domain using contrastive_learning.
// contrastive_learning trains on positive_pairs (similar) and negative_pairs (dissimilar).
// in_batch_negatives treats other examples in the same batch as implicit negatives.

// Primitive flow:
// embed_texts(["tekst 1", "tekst 2"], model) -> embedding_vectors [v1, v2]
// cosine_similarity(v1, v2) -> score in [-1, 1]
// most_similar(query_vec, corpus_vecs) -> top results by score
// semantic_cluster: embed all docs -> kmeans(k=20) -> cluster_assignment per doc
// semantic_dedup: for each pair (i,j): cosine_similarity > dedup_threshold -> mark j as duplicate
//   -> canonical_doc = first in each dedup_group
// dimensionality_reduction: embedding_matrix -> method_umap -> projection_2d -> visualization
// fine_tune: positive_pairs from domain data -> triplet_loss training -> specialized model

// This defines embedding generation, cosine similarity, clustering,
// dimensionality reduction, semantic deduplication, and cross-lingual alignment.

// ---- from runtime/z339.no ----
// Norscode Runtime - Omgang 339
// AI agent framework with tools and memory

runtime z339 {
  agent
  agent_id
  agent_name
  agent_description
  agent_system_prompt
