// Semantic direction:
// ai_observability extends OpenTelemetry (z326) with AI-specific span attributes.
// span_llm_call wraps one LLM API call with token counts, cost, latency, and prompt content.
// span_tool_call wraps one tool invocation within an agent run.
// attr_cost_usd tracks the dollar cost of each LLM call for budget monitoring.
// prompt_trace stores the full traced_messages and traced_response for debugging and replay.
// eval_suite is a named collection of eval_cases for testing an AI pipeline's quality.
// eval_case pairs a case_input with a golden case_expected and the measured case_output.
// evaluator scores each case using eval_fn: exact_match, regex, or llm_judge.
// llm_judge sends the judge_prompt (containing input, expected, and actual) to a judge_model.
// judge_score is a numeric rating (0–1); judge_reasoning explains the score.
// metric_faithfulness measures whether the answer is grounded in retrieved context.
// metric_hallucination detects claims not supported by any source document.
// metric_context_precision is the fraction of retrieved chunks that are actually relevant.
// metric_context_recall is the fraction of relevant chunks that were retrieved.
// eval_dataset holds the test set; golden_answer is the reference response.
// human_label is a quality rating provided by a human reviewer; label_agreement measures inter-rater reliability.
// regression_eval compares current_eval_result against baseline to detect quality regressions.
// eval_regression_threshold is the minimum score_delta that counts as a regression.
// ab_test_ai runs two prompt or model variants in parallel and compares ab_metric with statistical_significance.
// guardrail inspects inputs and outputs before they reach users.
// block_toxic rejects or filters harmful content; block_pii removes personal information.
// redact_pii replaces detected pii_type fields with placeholder tokens.
// prompt_injection_detect identifies attempts to override the system prompt.
// jailbreak_detect flags requests trying to circumvent safety constraints.

// Primitive flow:
// LLM call: ai_span(span_llm_call) -> record attr_model + tokens + latency + cost
// agent run: trace root span -> child spans per step (tool_call, embedding, retrieval)
// eval_suite run: for each eval_case:
//   run pipeline(case_input) -> case_output
//   evaluator(case_input, case_expected, case_output) -> case_score
//   llm_judge: build judge_prompt -> judge_model.complete -> judge_score + reasoning
// regression_eval: compare mean(current_scores) vs mean(baseline_scores)
//   -> score_delta < -threshold -> eval_regression_detected -> CI fail
// guardrail: every request -> guardrail_check(input) -> block or redact -> forward
//   every response -> guardrail_check(output) -> block toxic/PII before returning

// This defines AI observability, LLM cost tracking, automated evaluation
// with LLM-as-judge, regression detection, A/B testing, and guardrails.

