// Semantic direction:
// fine_tune adapts a pre-trained base model to a specific domain or task using training_data.
// ft_job is the training run; ft_result_model is the model produced after successful completion.
// training_example is one labeled sample: a message list (for chat models) or a prompt/completion pair.
// example_weight allows the trainer to emphasize certain examples relative to others.
// data_validate checks for formatting errors, token count limits, and class balance.
// ft_hyperparams control the training dynamics: learning_rate, batch_size, num_epochs.
// lora_rank and lora_alpha configure LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation), enabling efficient fine-tuning.
// LoRA adds small trainable matrices to attention layers, leaving base weights frozen.
// lora_target_modules specifies which layers receive LoRA adapters (q_proj, v_proj, etc.).
// ft_checkpoint saves model state at regular intervals; checkpoint_eval_loss guides selection.
// early_stopping halts training when eval_loss stops improving for patience steps.
// model_registry is the central store of all trained and versioned models.
// model_lineage tracks which parent_model and dataset produced each version.
// model_tags label models with their use case, training date, and eval metrics.
// promote_to_prod updates the production endpoint to serve the new model version.
// serve_canary_ml routes a fraction of traffic to the new model for A/B validation.
// serve_shadow runs the new model in parallel without returning its output to users.
// serve_rollback_ml reverts to the previous version if eval metrics degrade.
// continuous_training automatically retrains when data_drift or concept_drift is detected.
// data_drift is a statistical shift in the distribution of incoming requests.
// concept_drift is a change in the relationship between inputs and correct outputs.
// drift_threshold triggers retrain_pipeline when the measured drift exceeds the limit.

// Primitive flow:
// prepare: training_data (JSONL) -> data_validate -> data_stats (tokens, examples)
// ft_job: ft_config(base_model, dataset, hyperparams) -> submit to provider
// monitor: poll ft_status -> ft_status_running -> loss curves
//   early_stopping: eval_loss not improving for patience -> checkpoint_path saved
// ft_succeeded: ft_result_model -> model_registry.register
// model_compare: eval_both(candidate, current_prod) -> winner_model
// promote_to_prod: serve_canary_ml(10%) -> monitor metrics -> promote_full or rollback
// continuous_training: drift_detector -> drift > threshold -> retrain_pipeline

// This defines LLM fine-tuning with LoRA, model registry, versioned serving,
// canary promotion, and continuous training triggered by data drift.

