// Semantic direction:
// ai_app is a Norscode application that integrates one or more AI capabilities.
// ai_budget enforces spending limits; cost_tracker accumulates cost_records per request.
// budget_alert_threshold sends a notification before the daily limit is reached.
// ai_pipeline chains pipeline_stages into a composable processing graph.
// stage_preprocess cleans and normalizes input before embedding or generation.
// stage_postprocess formats, filters, or validates the LLM output before returning it.
// batch_processor handles bulk AI workloads: indexing documents, evaluating datasets, translating files.
// batch_parallel runs multiple items concurrently up to batch_parallel simultaneous requests.
// structured_output forces the model to return a JSON object matching output_schema.
// json_mode enables native JSON output on models that support it.
// tool_use_extraction uses a tool call to extract structured data from unstructured text.
// retry_on_invalid re-prompts the model with validation errors when the output fails schema check.
// classifier applies an LLM or smaller model to assign class_labels to text.
// zero_shot_classify uses the model's generalization without training examples.
// few_shot_classify provides labeled examples in the prompt to improve accuracy.
// summarizer condenses long text; summary_style controls the output format.
// extractive_summary selects key sentences verbatim; abstractive_summary paraphrases.
// translation converts text between languages while preserving formatting and formality.
// chat_interface manages an interactive multi-turn conversation with session state.
// inject_context_chat adds relevant documents or facts to the chat_context before each turn.
// norscode_ai_stdlib is the standard AI library included with Norscode.
// std_ai_llm exposes the llm_client; std_ai_embed exposes the embedder.
// std_ai_rag provides the full RAG pipeline as a standard library module.
// std_ai_agent provides the agent framework; std_ai_eval provides evaluation tools.
// nc_ai_command adds AI subcommands to the Norscode CLI.
// cmd_ai_run runs an agent or pipeline from the command line.
// cmd_ai_eval runs an eval_suite against a pipeline.
// cmd_ai_search queries the vector index from the terminal.

// Primitive flow:
// ai_pipeline.run(input):
//   stage_preprocess -> clean text
//   stage_embed -> embedding_vector
//   stage_retrieve -> top_k chunks
//   stage_rerank -> reranked chunks
//   stage_augment -> augmented_prompt
//   stage_generate -> llm completion
//   stage_postprocess -> formatted output
//   stage_evaluate -> faithfulness + relevance scores
// structured_output: request with output_schema -> json_mode or tool_use_extraction
//   -> parse_structured -> validate_structured
//   -> invalid? -> retry_on_invalid with error message
// batch_processor: batch_input list -> split into batches of batch_size_ai
//   -> batch_parallel concurrent requests -> collect batch_results
// nc ai run pipeline.no --input "query" -> run pipeline -> print output
// nc ai eval suite.no -> run eval_suite -> print scores + regression check

// This defines AI application patterns: pipelines, batch processing,
// structured output, classifiers, summarizers, and the Norscode AI stdlib.

